{"event_id": "fb56ed193d0c49feb8c31da25d241f41", "event_type": "tool_finished", "event_version": 1, "mission_id": "20260402-110233-982592-tiny-live-canary", "model": "openai/gpt-4.1-mini", "node_id": "root", "node_path": "/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/open-eywa/missions/live-canaries/20260402-110233-982592-tiny-live-canary/tree/root", "parent_node_id": null, "payload": {"output": {"content": "# Operator Note on Open-Eywa\n\nOpen-Eywa is a distributed task orchestration system designed to manage complex workflows by breaking them down into discrete, manageable units called nodes. Each node represents a durable unit of work that encapsulates a specific task or step within a larger mission.\n\n## Why the Node is the Durable Unit of Work\nThe node is the durable unit of work because it provides a clear boundary for task execution, state management, and fault tolerance. By isolating work into nodes, Open-Eywa ensures that progress is saved incrementally, enabling reliable recovery and continuation even if interruptions occur. This design simplifies tracking, debugging, and coordination across distributed systems.\n\n## Key Mission Files for Human Operators\nTo understand the mission state and progress, human operators should first inspect the following files:\n\n1. `input/context.md` - Provides the overall mission context, goals, and current state.\n2. `output/final-output.md` - Contains the final results or outputs generated by the node.\n3. `output/state.md` - Shows the current internal state or progress of the node.\n4. `input/parent-instructions.md` - Details the instructions or task assigned to the node.\n\nReviewing these files gives a comprehensive view of what the mission is about, what the node is working on, and what has been accomplished so far.\n\n---\n\nThis note should help operators quickly grasp the purpose and structure of Open-Eywa nodes and efficiently monitor mission progress.", "path": "children/step-01-write-operator-note-on-open-eywa/output/final-output.md"}, "tool_name": "read_file"}, "role": "mid-plan-evaluator", "run_id": "run-002", "timestamp_utc": "2026-04-02T05:17:53.932824Z", "variant": null}
